reviewText:
I wanted to like this game because I enjoy playing walking simulators.

However:
- as a native English speaker, I had absolutely no idea what was being said by the thickly-accented voice over, and once you factor in the invasive and sporadic jazz guitar solos, it's preferable to just mute the audio;
- in order to get a steady 60+ framerate on my GTX 970 I had to put the graphics settings to medium, even then it still dipped below 40 on occasion;
- no save points, meaning if you played the game for an hour, shut it down, came back to it, you would have to play it all over again to get to the same place.
